{{Infobox Officeholder |name = Aleksander Bobko |image = Aleksander Bobko Kancelaria Senatu 2015.jpg |office = [[Ministry of Science and Higher Education (Poland)|Deputy Minister of Science and Higher Education]] |term_start = 16 November 2015 |term_end = |predecessor = Marek Ratajczak |successor = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1960|3|23}} |birth_place = [[Warsaw]], [[People's Republic of Poland|Poland]] |death_date = |death_place = }}
'''Aleksander Bobko''' (born 23 March 1952) is the Deputy Minister of Science and Higher Education of [[Poland]]. He was previously the [[Rector (academia)|rector]] of [[Rzeszów University]].
==Biography== Bobko graduated in informatics from the [[AGH University of Science and Technology]]. He also earned advanced degrees in [[philosophy]], including a [[doctorate]] and a [[habilitation]], at the [[Pontifical University of John Paul II]] and at the [[Jagiellonian University]]. In the years 1998-2002, Bobko was a member of the [[city council]] of [[Rzeszów]].
He was affiliated with the Pontifical University of John Paul II, later joining the faculty at [[Rzeszów University]]. Bobko was vice dean (2002-2004) and dean (2004-2008) of the Faculty of Sociology and History, and then vice rector for research and international relations (2008-2012).
In 2009 Bobko was granted a state professorship of the humanities. In 2012 he was appointed [[Rector (academia)|rector]] of Rzeszów University, a position he held until 2015.
In 2015 he was elected to the [[Senate of Poland]]. Bobko was appointed as the Deputy Minister of Science and Higher Education on 16 November 2015.
